Package sml

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AddInstruction
    This class adds the contents of registers op1 and op2 and stores the result in register r, given the Instruction format: Label add r op1 op2
    BnzInstruction
    This class checks if the contents of register r is not zero, then makes the statement labelled Label2 the next one to execute Instruction Format: Label1 bnz r Label2
    DivInstruction
    This class divides the contents of registers op1 by op2 and stores the result in register r, given the Instruction format: Label div r op1 op2
    Instruction
    This class is the superclass of the classes for machine instructions
    Labels  
    LinInstruction
    This class stores the result x in register r, given the Instruction format: Label1 lin r x
    Machine  
    MulInstruction
    This class multiplies the contents of registers op1 and op2 and stores the result in register r, given the Instruction format: Label mul r op1 op2
    OutInstruction
    This class prints on the console the value in register s1, given the Instruction format: Label1 out s1
    Registers
    An instance of this class contains 32 registers and methods to access and change them.
    SubInstruction
    This class subtracts the contents of registers op1 from op2 and stores the result in register r, given the Instruction format: Label sub r op1 op2
